See notes under
A. boyacensis
.
Agrostis tolucensis
can sometimes have leaf blades wider than usual (up to 5 mm wide when opened out), but can usually be differentiated by a) the flag ligules being shorter, 2-4(-6.2) mm long (vs. 4-8 mm long in
A. foliata
); b) the spikelets often being shorter, 2-3(-3.6) mm long (vs. 3-4.2 mm long in
A. foliata
); c) florets usually over half the length of the glumes (vs. usually c. 1/2 the length of the glumes, rarely slightly longer in
A. foliata
); and d) primary panicle branches often shorter, 0.5-1.5 cm long, (vs. up to 7 cm long in
A. foliata
), among other characteristics.
